# ux_parity.me
# Purpose: UI/UX consistency rules across iOS and Android. Both platforms must
#          present the same information hierarchy, messaging, and feature behaviour.
#          Platform-native styling is allowed. Product behaviour is not.
# Scope: iOS (SwiftUI) and Android (Jetpack Compose or equivalent)

---

## 1. PRINCIPLE

Both apps are the same product. Visual styling may follow platform conventions.
Information hierarchy, action labels, status labels, error messages, and business
logic triggers must be identical across platforms.

---

## 2. GAME CARDS (Discovery, Club Games, Nearby)

### Must show on every game card:
- Game title
- Date and time (formatted for user locale)
- Venue name
- Skill level badge
- Spots remaining (e.g. "3 spots left") or "Full" badge
- Fee badge: "$12 AUD" or "Free"
- "Waitlist" label when game is full and waitlist is available

### Scheduled (unpublished) games — admin/owner view only:
- Dimmed at ~55% opacity
- Orange "Not visible to the public · Goes live in Xd Yh Zm" banner
- Countdown refreshed every 60 seconds (not on every render)
- Hidden entirely from player/public view

### Full game behaviour:
- Show "Join Waitlist" CTA when game is full
- Do NOT show a "Book" CTA when no spots remain
- Waitlist position shown after joining: "You are #X on the waitlist"

---

## 3. BOOKING STATES — CTA AND LABELS

Both platforms must use the same CTA labels and visual hierarchy per booking state:

| State | CTA Label | Visual |
|---|---|---|
| Can book (free) | "Book Now" | Primary action |
| Can book (paid, no credits) | "Book · $X.XX" | Primary action |
| Can book (paid, partial credits) | "Book · $X.XX" (net price) | Primary action; credit line below |
| Can book (full credit cover) | "Book with Credits" | Primary action |
| Confirmed | "Booked" (disabled) | Success state |
| Waitlisted | "On Waitlist · #X" (disabled) | Neutral state |
| pending_payment (active hold) | "Complete Booking · $X.XX" | Orange/urgent; countdown below |
| pending_payment (expired hold) | "Spot hold expired" (passive) | Grey; Refresh button nearby |
| Cannot book (past game) | No CTA | Informational only |

Credit toggle row:
- Shown when: `fee > 0 AND creditBalance(for: clubID) > 0 AND canBook`
- Label: "Apply Credits ($X.XX available)"
- Net price reflected immediately in CTA label when toggled on

---

## 4. PAYMENT BADGES (Admin/Owner View)

Shown in the attendee list. Visible to club admin and owner only — not players.

| Payment Method | Label | Colour |
|---|---|---|
| `"stripe"` | "Card" | Blue |
| `"admin"` | "Comp" | Grey |
| NULL (free game) | "Free" | Light grey |
| NULL (paid game, not paid) | "Unpaid" | Orange |

---

## 5. CANCELLATION FEEDBACK

After a player cancels:
- If credit was issued: show a half-sheet or modal with:
  - "Credit issued: $X.XX"
  - "New balance: $X.XX"
  - Dismiss button
- If no credit (within 6h window): show brief confirmation ("Booking cancelled") with no credit mention
- The 6-hour window message must be shown BEFORE the player cancels, not after

Pre-cancel warning copy (when within 6h window):
> "Cancelling within 6 hours of the game start — no credit will be issued."

Pre-cancel confirmation copy (when outside 6h window and credit eligible):
> "You will receive a $X.XX credit for this booking."

---

## 6. WAITLIST HOLD FEEDBACK

When a player is promoted from the waitlist:
- Push notification copy: "A spot opened — complete your booking"
- On game detail, show countdown: "X m Ys remaining to complete your booking"
- Countdown updates every second
- On expiry: replace countdown with "Spot hold expired" and a Refresh button
- Do NOT auto-navigate or auto-present PaymentSheet on push notification tap — player must tap the CTA

---

## 7. CREDIT DISPLAY

### On game detail:
- Credit balance line shown below price: "You have $X.XX in credits for this club"
- Credit toggle appears when eligible (see §3)

### On club detail:
- Credit banner shown between membership section and club info
- Refreshed on appear and pull-to-refresh
- Format: "You have $X.XX in credits at this club"
- Hidden when balance = 0

### On bookings list:
- One pill per club with positive balance
- Format: "$X.XX at [Club Name]"
- All balances refreshed concurrently on view load

---

## 8. NOTIFICATIONS TAB

- Separate navigation stack for the Notifications tab
- Club destinations navigate inline (Back returns to Notifications)
- Game destinations open as modal/bottom sheet (dismiss returns to Notifications)
- "Clear All" button available
- Chevron/arrow shown on notification rows only when a destination exists
- Review notifications are always tappable (no in-memory game required)

---

## 9. CLUB OWNER TOOLS MENU

Order is standardised. Both platforms must use this exact order:
1. View / Edit Games
2. Create Game
3. [Separator]
4. Club Settings
5. [Separator]
6. Join Requests
7. Manage Members

---

## 10. REVIEWS SECTION (Club Detail)

- Show star average + review count above individual reviews
- Show at most 2 reviews initially; "Show more" to expand
- Each review shows: star rating, reviewer initials, game title context, comment, date
- Section hidden until at least one review exists
- Review prompt appears as a notification 24h after game ends
- Review sheet header = game title; review is about the club (not the game)
- On duplicate submit: "You have already left a review for this session." (not a generic error)

---

## 11. CLUB CHAT

- Post button label changes contextually:
  - Default mode: "Post" (or send icon)
  - Announcement mode active: "Announce" (or announcement icon)
- Announcement toggle becomes icon-only when active (compact UI)
- Comment draft is per-card, not per-feed (no cross-card state sharing)
- Optimistic UI: likes and comment counts update immediately

---

## 12. GAME RESULT POSTS

- Game results are structured JSON payloads — NOT image-based posts
- Result card rendered natively (not as an image)
- Result card shows: game title, date, teams, scores, winner
- Sharing exports as an image (for social) but the in-app post is always a native card
- Structured post detected via `post.type == "session_result"`

---

## 13. ERROR STATES

Consistent error messaging across platforms:

| Scenario | Message |
|---|---|
| Stripe payment failed | "Payment failed. Please try again." |
| Network unavailable | "No internet connection. Please check your connection." |
| Booking full on submit | "This game is now full. You've been added to the waitlist." |
| Hold expired | "Your spot hold expired. Please refresh to rejoin the waitlist." |
| Duplicate review | "You have already left a review for this session." |
| Credit deduction failed | "Could not apply credits. Please try again." |
| Generic error | "Something went wrong. Please try again." |

---

## VIOLATION IMPACT
- Inconsistent CTA labels → players confused about booking state; support volume increases.
- Showing credit balance cross-club → player attempts to use credits at wrong club; booking fails silently.
- Hiding admin payment badges from admins → admins can't track unpaid players.
- Different cancellation window messages → legal/financial disputes about when credits are owed.
- Missing hold countdown → player doesn't know they have a time limit; hold expires unnoticed.
